parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
the brakes lock up or fail to engage
the vehicle slides or skids when braking
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
or the brakes make a grinding or squealing noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes do not engage
the vehicle takes longer to stop
or the brakes make a grinding or squealing noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pads can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pads grind into the caliper
the brakes make a grinding or squealing noise
or the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause reduced visibility during rain or snow, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Windshield wipers work intermittently
stop working during operation
fail to turn on
or turn on and off sporadically
reducing driver visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rearview mirror can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when changing lanes or merging with traffic.
symptoms: The rearview mirror pops out or falls off while driving
reducing driver visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torsion bar can cause the vehicle to drop, making it difficult or impossible to steer, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's front end drops
the tire rubs against the wheel well
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering becomes difficult
the vehicle is unable to turn
a loud popping or snapping noise is heard.
